Title: Welcome
Event (140 words): Enjoy the WWII Explorer App. Click "Start Exploring" to begin the journy
kml_file: Germany.kml, Japan.kml, Italy.kml, Russia.kml, United_States.kml, United_Kingdom.kml, France.kml

Title: Japan invades Manchuria
Event (140 words): In response to a staged rail line attack, Japan invades north-eastern China as part of a continous struggle between the two contries.

Title: Hitler comes to power
Event (140 words): Adolf Hitler appointed as Chancellor of Germany, quickly using this power to gain control of the different branches of the German government.

Title: Jewish persecution in Germany
Event (140 words): Jewish owned shops and businesses are boycotted in Germany, identifying the Jewish people as inferior.

Title: Italy conquers Ethiopia
Event (140 words): Sparked by a border conflict with Italy controlled Somalia, Fascist Italy invades, conquers, and annexes Ethiopia.

Title: Axis Powers Formed
Event (140 words): Nazi Germany and Fascist Italy sign a treaty of cooperation. Rome-Berlin Axis is announced

Title: Japan joins Axis Powers
Event (140 words): Imperial Japan joins Nazi Germany and Facist Italy, with the common goal of the post-World War I international order and to neutralize the Communist movement.

Title: Japan invades China
Event (140 words): Known as the second Sino-Japanses war, with fighting that continued through the duration of World War II.

Title: Italy invades and annexes Albania
Event (140 words): Fascist Italy invades and annexes Albania, in efforts to keep up with Germany's military efforts.

Title: Germany invades Poland
Event (140 words): German forces bombard Poland, using the blitzkrieg military strategy, seeking to regain lost territory.

Title: Britain and France declared war on Germany
Event (140 words): In response to the invasion on Poland, Great Britain and France declare war on Germany.

Title: Germany invades Denmark, Norway, Holland and Belgium
Event (140 words): Germany pushes military efforts through western Europe, invading Denmark, Norway, Holland (Netherlands), and Belgium.
kml_file: Germany.kml, Denmark.kml, Norway.kml, Belgium.kml, Netherlands.kml, event11.kml

Title: Miracle of Dunkirk
Event (140 words): British forces are pushed to the shores of Dunkirk, northern France. Over 338,000 Allied soldiers were evacuated in eight days.

Title: Germany takes Paris, France
Event (140 words): Having defeated Poland, Germany invades France in six weeks. Germany is now unmatched on mainland Europe.

Title: Battle of Britian
Event (140 words): Germany battles British forces for air superiority, bombing military and civillian targets. Britian maintains air superiority, preventing a land invasion.

Title: Italy invades Greece
Event (140 words): Italy invades Greece from Albania. This uncoordinated attack proves to weaken the Italian forces, as they should have been focused on another front.

Title: Italians defeated in North Africa
Event (140 words): British reinforcements in North Africa stop the Italian forces from progressing further into Africa.

Title: Germany invades Russia (Operation Barbarossa)
Event (140 words): Germany invades Russia in the largest military operation in history (manpower and casualties). After massive initial success, the German army stall short of Moscow.

Title: Germans driven back by Soviets
Event (140 words): A Soviet counteroffensive drives the Germans from the Moscow suburbs and chaotic retreat.

Title: Japanese attack Pearl Harbor
Event (140 words): The suprise attack aims to stop American interference in Japanese Imperial expansion, leading to America's involvement in World War II.

Title: Britian and United States declare war on Japan
Event (140 words): In response to the bombing at Pearl Harbor, President Roosevelt and Winston Churchill declare war on Japan.

Title: Japanese conquer Burma
Event (140 words): The Japanese push through Burma (Myanmar), hoping to raise an insurrection in India against the British.

Title: Japan occupies Pacific territories
Event (140 words): Japanese occupies Philippines, Vietnam, Laos, Cambodia, British Singapore with troops.
kml_file: Philippines.kml, Vietnam.kml, Laos.kml, Cambodia.kml, Singapore.kml, Japan.kml, event22.kml

Title: British bomb Germany
Event (140 words): The British bomb Germany and urban cities. Bombing continued for next three years by Allied forces.

Title: Battle of Midway Island
Event (140 words): The forwarned US navy decisively defeats the Imperial Japanese navy at Midway Atoll.

Title: US Troops Advance in Pacific
Event (140 words): US troops halt the Japanese island-hopping advance towards Australia at Guadalcanal in the Solomon Islands

Title: Battle of Stalingrad, Russia
Event (140 words): German forces begin attacks on Stalingrad, hoping to sieze the industrial town and place a better foot hold in Russia.

Title: Battle of El Alamein, Egypt
Event (140 words): British troops defeat the Germans and Italians at El Alemein in Egypt, sending the Axis forces in chaotic retreat across Libya to the eastern border of Tunisia.

Title: German army surrenders at Stalingrad
Event (140 words): The German army makes advances in South Russia, but is halted at Stalingrad. One of the bloddiest battles ever ensues and eventually Germand surrenders.

Title: Axis forces surrendered North Africa
Event (140 words): Axis forces in Tunisia surrender to the Allies, ending the North African campaign.

Title: Allies invade Italy
Event (140 words): US and British troop land in Sicily, Italy. Allies control Sicily by August 1943

Title: Italy surrenders
Event (140 words): Mussolini is deposed from power and Italy surrenders their war efforts.

Title: Allies hold Tehran Conference
Event (140 words): President Roosevelt, Prime Minister Churchill, and Premier Stalin meet to discuss post-war internatioal organizational plans.

Title: D-Day (Operation Overlord)
Event (140 words): The Allies launch the largest amphibious assult in history on Normandy. Over 1 million men are landed and and a new front against Germany is opened.

Title: Allies push past Normandy
Event (140 words): Allies break out of the Normandy beachhead and race eastward towars Paris, France.

Title: Paris liberated
Event (140 words): Paris is freed from Germany's 4 year dominion, with German troops surrendering or fleeing from battle.

Title: US Troops in Philippines
Event (140 words): US Troops land in the Philippines, revisiting a front which was lost two years prior.

Title: Battle of the Bulge
Event (140 words): German forces launch a final offensive in the west in an attempt to re-conquer Belgium and split the Allied forces. The German counteroffensive is neutralized by January 1945.

Title: America captures Iwo Jima
Event (140 words): US forces successfully capture Iwo Jima island. The US overwhelming supremacy in arm and men guarentreed a decisive but costly victory.

Title: Mussolini captured and executed
Event (140 words): Attempting to escape the country for his war crimes, Mussolini and his mistress fail to leave and are executed.

Title: Hitler commits suicide
Event (140 words): With Soviet troops advancing in Germany, Hitler commit suicide in his underground bunker.

Title: Russia takes Berlin, Germany
Event (140 words): Germany troop yield to Russian troops, at the battle torn city of Berlin falls under Russia's control.

Title: Germany surrenders
Event (140 words): Without Hitler to command the German forces, Germany surrenders to the western Allies.

Title: Atomic bombs dropped on Hiroshima and Nagasaki
Event (140 words): Japan's refusal to surrender led to the decision to drop two atomic bombs on Hiroshima and Nagasaki. There are mixed feelings about the use of the nuclear weapons, a discussion that continues to date.

Title: End of World War II
Event (140 words): Japan surrenders unconditionally in August 14 1945, formally surrendering in September. The war is over.
kml_file: Germany.kml, Japan.kml, Italy.kml, Russia.kml, United_States.kml, United_Kingdom.kml, France.kml
